                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Pto Cabello</placeName>\n                                        <date>24 March 1854</date>.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Dear Sir!</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have the pleasure to acknowledge the\n                                        receipt<lb/> of your favor of <date>23d</date> last covering\n                                        b/Ly for 1 box containing<lb/> 2 cops bibles, 1 do\n                                                  <sic>payer</sic> books 1 do Bible and two do\n                                                  <persName>Dias</persName><lb/> letters per Paez,\n                                                  <persName>Capt<hi rend=\"sup\">n</hi>\n                                                  Wilkins</persName> amtg to $66.37 ½ for which<lb/>\n                                        together with the contribution to the Occident for the\n                                        com<lb/>ing year, I beg leave to enclose a draft on\n                                                  <persName>Messrs Dallett<lb/> Brothers</persName>\n                                        at your port say $69.384. The bibles and<lb/> prayerbooks\n                                        were all to my liking, only in the prospec<lb/>tus sent to\n                                        you please to observe that only one copy was<lb/> ordered\n                                        with any name; fortunately it happened that<lb/> the other\n                                        was for a very particular and intimate friend<lb/> of mine,\n                                        who would have no objection to take it even<lb/> with my\n                                        name, as he did without hesitancy. One copy<lb/> of\n                                                  <persName>Dias'</persName> letters I took for\n                                        myself, and the other toge<lb/>ther with the unordered copy\n                                        of the bible was taken<lb/> by <persName>Mr Jacob\n                                                  Julien</persName> of this place; and I will try to\n                                        dis<lb/>pose of some of your books among my friends here\n                                        &amp;<lb/> about, and succeeding which I sincerely hope I\n                                        may,<lb/> I will immediately advise you of the same.</p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">On the</hi>\n                              </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p37m04k90/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
